### OhData TestBench — sample HTTP requests (movies demo)
### Use VS Code REST Client or JetBrains HTTP Client
### Start with: dotnet run --project src/OhData.TestBench.AspNetCore

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5099

# ── Service documents & metadata ─────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v2

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/$metadata

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/$metadata

###

# ── Movies — collection queries (GetQueryable, SQL pushdown) ─────────────────

### All movies
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies

###

### Filter + orderby + top + select -- recognizable real movies, synthetic ratings
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies?$filter=year gt 2000 and rating gt 8&$orderby=rating desc&$top=5&$select=title,year,rating

###

### Filter by genre
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies?$filter=genreCode eq 'SCIFI'&$orderby=year

###

### Page: skip 10, take 5
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies?$skip=10&$top=5&$orderby=id

###

### Inline count with filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies?$count=true&$filter=genreCode eq 'ACTION'

###

### Count endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies/$count

###

# ── Movies — single item + ETag ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get by id -- note the ETag response header (UseETag(Id, UpdatedAt))
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(1)

###

### Get non-existent id → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(9999)

###

### If-Match: read the ETag above, then PATCH with it -- succeeds (200)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(1)
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "paste-the-etag-value-from-the-GET-above"

{
  "rating": 9.5
}

###

### Same PATCH with a stale/wrong If-Match → 412 Precondition Failed
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(1)
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "not-the-current-etag"

{
  "rating": 1.0
}

###

# ── Movies — bound operations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### TopRated: collection-bound function, GET with query-string params
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies/TopRated?count=5

###

### Rate: entity-bound action, POST with a JSON body -- folds into a running average
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(1)/Rate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 9.8
}

###

# ── Movies — write operations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a movie (v1 -- AllowDeepInsert is false; any "cast" here would be stripped)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "A New Feature",
  "year": 2025,
  "rating": 7.5,
  "runtimeMinutes": 118,
  "genreCode": "DRAMA",
  "studioId": 1,
  "releaseDate": "2025-01-01"
}

###

### Update a movie (replace)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(1)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Godfather",
  "year": 1972,
  "rating": 9.3,
  "runtimeMinutes": 175,
  "genreCode": "CRIME",
  "studioId": 7,
  "releaseDate": "1972-03-24"
}

###

### Delete a movie
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/Movies(79)

###

# ── Genres — simple GetAll (string key) ────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Genres

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Genres('SCIFI')

###

# ── v2: deep insert, Cast/Studio navigation, $expand, $ref ────────────────────

### Deep insert: AllowDeepInsert = true on v2 -- nested "cast" entries are linked to
### EXISTING actors by id (23 = Leonardo DiCaprio, 24 = Kate Winslet in the seed data)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "A New Feature",
  "year": 2025,
  "rating": 7.5,
  "runtimeMinutes": 118,
  "genreCode": "DRAMA",
  "studioId": 1,
  "releaseDate": "2025-01-01",
  "cast": [ { "id": 23 }, { "id": 24 } ]
}

###

### $expand=cast -- per-entity fallback (see MovieProfileV2's Cast comment for why)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies(1)?$expand=cast

###

### $expand=studio -- batch-loaded (one query for the whole page, see CLAUDE.md)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies?$filter=id eq 1&$expand=studio

###

### $expand=movies on Studios -- the reverse batch-loaded navigation
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Studios?$filter=id eq 7&$expand=movies

###

### GET the current cast for a movie
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies(1)/Cast

###

### $ref add: link an existing actor (id 40) to a movie's Cast
POST {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies(1)/Cast/$ref
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "@odata.id": "Actors(40)"
}

###

### $ref remove: unlink an actor from a movie's Cast
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v2/Movies(1)/Cast/$ref?$id=Actors(40)

###

### Actors and Studios are queryable entity sets in v2 (not in v1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Actors?$filter=birthYear gt 1980&$orderby=name

###

GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Studios

###

# ── Versioning — v1 doesn't have Actors/Studios ───────────────────────────────

### Actors exist in v2
GET {{baseUrl}}/v2/Actors(1)

###

### Actors do not exist in v1 → 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/Actors

###
